         <abstract id="aspace_0f44fe6556ca022f6cdb18cf7dc63180">Pre-Columbian Architecture, Ceramics, Metalwork, and Sculpture Photograph Collection 1,055 photographs, black and white unless otherwise specified, mounted and unmounted, in a variety of sizes. Many were gifts from the Latin American Studies Council. Photos are of architecture, ceramics, metalwork, sculpture, and wall paintings from Central and South America. Their purchase dates span the life of the Visual Resources Collection, ca. 1940-1995. Assembled as a consulting collection for materials not in the general slide and photograph holdings. Includes photography by the Peruvian photographer, Abraham Guillen.</abstract>
